ICAO FLIGHT PLAN


~a) Entering items into the form~: each column is to
   be filled with approved characters  only
   (e.g. definition time is done with figures only).
   Command keys:

   "Moving cursor among items of the form"
   ~Tab, Enter~  move to the following item
   ~Shift Tab~   return to  the porevious item
   ~Ctrl Home~   the first item in the form
   ~Ctrl End~    the last item in the form
   ~Ctrl |,~  move to any of the items

   "Editing"
   ~Ins(ert)~    changing  modes enter /insert
   ~Del(ete)~    erasing  character under the cursor
   ~BS~          cancelling character before the cursor

   ~Ctrl Del~    erasing a complete item
   ~Alt  Del~    erasing all items in the form

   "End of planning" ?????????????
   ~Esc~         cancellation



MIL FPL

~FILING AND PROCESSING OF MILTARY FLIGHT PLANS~

~b) Item contents~: Before confirmation all important items
   of the plans are checked. It might be helpful to know
   that if the ~I~"ndex" changeover button appears, when
   moving cursor onto a form item, then one can present
   "index" -  offer of approved values - using ~Alt~+~I~
   (~Ctrl~+~F1~).

   ~Caution !~ In accordance with the mode set, Enter/Insert,
   the text is put on the cursor position and the rest
   of the line is either shifted or erased.

   When defining route the following changeover switches
   are presented:

   ~P~"oints" - selection of turning point
   ~O~"ver"   - instructions to activities or changes
             in flight parameters over TP (see further)
   ~R~"oute"  - route presentation


~c) entering  route~: a route plan is a sentence made up
   of words, separated by spacings. The words are formed
   by groups of characters separated by "/". The first
   part of the word defines the turning point. There are
   five options available:

   "501"          - TP  Code  by the dial
   "JEL"          - Code of the radionav point by the AIP
   "LZPP"         - Airfield Code by the dial or by the AIP
   "Z123"         - LDM Code
   "492312190034" - latitude and longitude that can be
                  separated by "-".

   There is possible to specify actions, changes on the TP
   by the following instructions:

   "/L"    delay over TP against the plan - in minutes
         for delay message
   "/C"    time spent over the TP - in minutes

   "/A"    arrival to TP - hour:min
   "/D"    departure from TP - hour:min

   "/V"    change in speed over TP
   "/H"    change in altitude  over TP in tens of metres
         STD or QNH
   "/G"    change in terrain clearance  in tens of metres
         (terrain clearance up to 300  over terrain)

   "/MZP"  stopover (defining time in minutes is available)
   "/STH"  from this point on to the  next flight as far as
         to the state border

   "/IP"   from this point  on, to the next flight within the
         identification area

   "/DES"  descent over TP  (only informative)
   "/ASC"  climb over TP (only informative)


      Change in flight parameters over TP also changes the
   hitherto valid flight parameters (altitude, speed).
      Change in time references (due to delay, activities
   over the turning point, stopover, arrival, departure)
   results in recalculation of arrival time data over next
   points of the flight planned route.
      Symptoms "D" and "A" enjoy highest priority when
   calculating arrival time an departure to (from) the point.
   If time "A" is less than the time of departure from the
   latest point or time "D" is less than the time of arrival
   to the point, the programme takes it for time data
   relating to the next day. The same can be achieved if
   symptoms "A" or "D" are followed  by  "+".

      On a point, only one specification of activities
   of the same kind (the last one) can be valid.


EN-ROUTE FLIGHT PLAN

~FILING, CORRECTING ATS-ROUTE FLIGHT PLANS~

~a) Entering items into the form.~ The columns can be
   filled with approved characters only. Command keys
   of entering data:

   "Moving cursor among items"

   ~Tab, Enter~  move to the next item
   ~Shift Tab~   return to the previous item
   ~Ctrl Home~   the first item in  ther form
   ~Ctrl End~    the last item in the form
   ~Ctrl |,~  move to other item 

   "Editing"
   ~Ins(ert)~    switching modes enter/insert
   ~Del(ete)~    erasing character under the cursor
   ~BS~          cancelling character before the cursor

   ~Ctrl Del~    erasing an entire item
   ~Alt  Del~    erasing all items in the form

   "End of planning"
   ~Alt  S~      distribution of plans
   ~Alt  U~      confirmation of plans and their tracking
   ~Esc~         cancellation

b) If there there is more than one turning point defined,
   the editor einquires wether it is to recalculate the route:

   ~L~"AST -> ..." - starting with the recent turning point
   ~N~"EXT -> ..." - starting with the next  turning point

   ~E~"ST"         - the entire plan
   "N"~O~"PL"      - without calculation

FILLING THE FPL

Compiling  EST message with respect to either civilian
or military FPL.

EN-ROUTE CHANGE

Rerouting of a plan selected.

CANCELLING FPL

Cancelling strip from the EDD and RDP monitors.

PREVIEW OF FPLs

Preview of all FPLs of selected types.

RECEIVED STRIPS

Setting strip confirmation and printing strips received.

ACCEPTED STRIPS

Setting mode of processing and presenting strips:

~T~"ABLET" - setting strip sequencing and presentation
~N~"DB"    - setting beacon positions in the tablet
~F~"PL"    - setting strip processing parameters.

SETTING THE TABLET

Setting mode of strip processing and presentation:

~I~"NPUT NDB" - sequencing strips on entry beacon
            or on the active beacon
~E~"MPTY NDB" - presenting list with the beacon,
            even without any aircraft inbound

~D~"IRECTION" - introducing  a coloured underlay
            in accordance with flight direction
              - red for EAST->WEST,
              - grey for WEST->EAST
~A~"LTIDUDE FL/M" - changeover switch of altitude
            presentation in meters
            or in flight level
~M~"IL STRIP" - writing out military route in line
            form or with turning points and time
            calculated

STRIP TAKEOVER

~A~"CCEPT"  - introducing strip into the tablet
~D~"ECLINE" - cancelling strip

STRIP PROCESSING

~R~"TE"   -  ammmending route
~L~"AM"   -  presenting LASM message
~C~"NL"   -  cancelling strip from  EDD and  RDP monitors
~V~"IEW"  -  writing out  the entire plan for the strip
~P~"RINT" -  printing out strip

ROUTE CALCULATION

While ammending a civilian strip it is possible
to recalculate  the route applying:

~L~"AST -> ..." - starting with the recent point
~N~"EXT -> ..." - starting with the next  point 

~E~"ST"         - entire plan
"N"~O~"PL"      - without recalculation

TABLET

Sequencing  beacons into a column can be set while
running the programme. The comments show which of
the columns is edited. Beacons are written out
starting from the lower one.

Indication of other types of beacons:
 "MIL"   - military flights
 "FPL"   - nor nilitary nor en-route flights
 "OTHER" - flights that cannot be assigned to none
         of the beacons
 "NOPL"  - flights  with no routes asssigned

